            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Yeah I think limiting technological determinism to the Singularitarians is a bit unfair to a more secular interpretation, like what I'd subscribe to. I'd simply say that when we design technologies our early choices constrain our later choices. In this case Internet Explorer thwarted web standards for about a decade, creating a Flash-shaped space awaiting the right combination of random factors. (Which turned out to be pretty random indeed--Flash being the team-up of a prodigy who would ship three historically-important graphics apps before the age of thirty and an Olympic pistol shooter with high tech literacy and a lot of investment income.)"
              }
